-- Aqua America to Boost Dividend After Second-Quarter Income Gain
-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m
-- 2013-08-07T14:37:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-07/aqua-america-to-boost-dividend-after-second-quarter-income-gain.html
Aqua America Inc. (WTR) , the second-largest
U.S. water utility by market value, will boost its dividend
after second-quarter income increased.  Aqua America will raise its quarterly dividend 9 percent to
19 cents a share effective Sept. 1, the Bryn Mawr, Pennsylvania-based company said in a statement yesterday. Net income rose to
$53.6 million, or 38 cents per share, from $41.4 million, or 30
cents, in 2012.  American Water Works Co. is the largest U.S. water utility.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Justin Doom in  New York  at 
